 in-house?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Dr. Jeff Muszynski places and restores dental implants at Elm Ridge Implant and Family Dentistry in Killeen, so planning, surgery, and final teeth can be coordinated by one team."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you offer All-on-4 or fixed full-arch implant teeth?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. We evaluate patients for fixed full-arch implant options, including All-on-4-style treatment, as well as removable implant-retained options."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you offer snap-on implant dentures?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Snap-on implant dentures can improve stability for patients who want a removable denture that attaches to implants."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much do dental implants cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cost depends on the number of implants, whether extractions or bone grafting are needed, the type of final teeth, materials, and the overall complexity of the case. We review cost after an exam and CBCT-based consultation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I be sedated for implant treatment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Elm Ridge offers nitrous oxide and oral conscious sedation for appropriate candidates. Not everyone is a candidate, but everyone is welcome to be evaluated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why do you use CBCT imaging?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CBCT imaging helps evaluate bone and anatomy in 3D, which is important for precise implant planning and avoiding critical structures."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long do dental implants take to heal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most implant cases need about 3 to 4 months of healing before the final restoration. Some grafting or sinus cases may take longer."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are dental implants painful?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients are numbed for implant placement. Soreness, swelling, or tenderness can happen afterward, but the visit is planned to keep the experience controlled and comfortable."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens if I don't replace a missing tooth?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Over time, nearby teeth can drift, opposing teeth can over-erupt, and the bone in the missing-tooth site can shrink. That can make future treatment more involved than it would have been earlier."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can teeth shift after losing a tooth?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Teeth can lean into the open space and the opposing tooth can start moving farther out, which is one reason replacing a missing tooth is often easier sooner than later."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does bone loss matter for dental implants?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Dental implants need enough bone for stable placement. If bone shrinks after tooth loss, grafting may become more likely before the implant can be placed."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I finance dental implant treatment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. We can help you understand implant insurance, out-of-pocket costs, and financing options so the decision is based on real numbers instead of guessing."}}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Service","name":"Dental Implants","description":"Dental implant placement and restoration in Killeen, TX","provider":{"@id":"https://www.elmridgedental.com/#dentist"},"areaServed":["Killeen TX","Harker Heights TX","Copperas Cove TX","Belton TX","Temple TX","Salado TX"]}</script></head>
